      "message": "Patch Set 5: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI have some small concern about mapping FID_SEQ_DOT_LUSTRE to MDT0 on the client instead of inside the FLDB, since this just adds a special case to the code that could instead be handled by an existing mechanism.\n\nIs it just that FID_SEQ_DOT_LUSTRE is not added to the FLDB currently, or why does the client need to special case this?  If it is a defect in the current MDT initialization that this is not in the FLDB, then that is something that should also be fixed in the MDS setup code, and eventually the client-side workaround can be removed...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "de902a30d39937164665d0f3602d2919a0cb7749",
      "author": {
